{
  "stem": "12150.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They ate one slice at night and one slice in the morning with the bitter coffee, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So they divided it so they have it for two days, sort of.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And this went on until on the third day, I-- I started to eat the soup, or what they called soup.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But little by little, I got used to it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And this is how we spent the first week in Auschwitz, sitting in the sun and talking, and hoping that the war will be over, which was a dream at that time.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was in-- in the middle of '44, so it was very far from over.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In the meantime, once in a while I met people from the same town marching by, doing some work.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I asked about my sisters, and nobody knew.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But my parents-- when I was a different transport, because I was from a different town, and nobody knew anything.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But we met old-- haftling means prisoner in German.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Haftling.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "H-A-F-T-L-I-N-G.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We met all the prisoners, Jewish, possibly Polish people, have been there for two years.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they didn't encourage us at all.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They-- they said, if your group is going to be shipped out of Auschwitz, you have a slight chance of survival.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "If your group-- but the percentage-- this guy was from Poland and he talked-- you know, he talked.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He said, the-- all the newcomers are dreaming the war will be over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And by that time, there will be nothing left of you.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "You don't have to worry about that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So-- and he gave us a few tips how to obey orders, not to fight the kapo or blockalteste.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "That's a block leader.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "That is a German.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Every barracks had a German in charge of the kapo.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
